data.title: Sweet treat
data.text: Delicious doughnuts! I had the chocolate iced cream filled and my mom had the a pumpkin cake with cream cheese frosting. Yum!

data.title: A doughnut is a doughnut, square or round.
data.text: I stopped by here yesterday to check this place out.  I thought the selection of donuts in the display area was relatively limited.  But what I had tasted good. I liked the feel of inside eating area and the outside of the shop has been well done.  I would definitely go here for fresh donuts ahead of the large grocery store bakeries and the upscale bakery down the street.  A square donut still tastes like a round one and that's really good.

data.title: Finally, donuts that fit in the box
data.text: I went to Square Donuts for my first time to see what the hype was about. I got there early and found a fully stocked case of fresh donuts. I was amazed that they could convert an old house into a bakery. The donut selection wasn't as large as Taylor's but they had all of my favorites. The donuts were good and I felt they were a good value.

data.title: "Is it 'Donut Saturday, or what ?"
data.text: My granddaughter convinced me that Square Donuts was worth the visit, so we stopped there to select some donut treats.  She loves the ones with the sprinkles on top, probably because those are colorful and tasty.  I love chocolate, so that is the ones that I selected.  These donuts are fresh, tasty and competitively priced.  For those people that simply cannot pass up a donut shop, this is the place to go.

data.title: Wanted to tryout
data.text: My Little Pony nice little family owned place to grab a snack nice sitting and relax for a while..... you will have to try the apple filled omg so good but they sale out fast

data.title: Busy little place and for good reason
data.text: We just picked up a box of square doughnuts on the way out of town and they were amazing.  Not too sticky.  Just right.  Great icing and their shape seems to make for a bigger treat.  Not cheap, but you get your money's worth, for sure.  Many for trips there to come.
